    "The overall speedup is modeled as a composition of changes in data collection, GPU data transfer, kernel computation and update data based on results.",
    "Furthermore, our data redundancy approach enhances sub-problem independence by localizing memory accesses, making it naturally compatible with existing hybrid or clusterbased MLFMA frameworks -where improved thread-level autonomy reduces inter-node synchronization pressure and facilitates integration into large-scale GPU-accelerated systems.",
